Message.Title: New ads are brilliant! Just bought more
Message.Msg: I just bought a new car and I was amazed at how brilliantly GOOG helped me with targeted ads. They could tell I was buying an electric so I got a lot of really helpful ads that followed my decision making as I gradually decided to buy a Chevy volt. The early ads showed me other alternatives but as I converged on the Volt the ads narrowed down to Chev dealers and used car slide shows of Volts. These were painlessly slipped into the margins of various websites who were paid for the space. This is the way advertising should be: helpful and unobtrusive. Hopefully, I'll pay for the car with the money I make by investing in GOOG. They really have this figured out and I'm sure it will show in their bottom line.
